President Obama announced his intent to nominate several individuals to key administration posts. William R. Brownfield was nominated for Assistant Secretary for International Narcotics and Law Enforcement Affairs at the Department of State. Gene L. Dodaro was nominated for Comptroller General of the United States at the Government Accountability Office. Matthew Maxwell Taylor Kennedy was nominated for Member of the Board of Directors of the Overseas Private Investment Corporation. Kurt Walter Tong was nominated for the rank of Ambassador during his tenure as United States Senior Coordinator for the Asia Pacific Economic Cooperation Forum at the Department of State. President Obama also announced his intent to appoint several individuals to serve on the United States Holocaust Memorial Council. The appointees include Tom Bernstein as Chair, Joshua Bolten as Vice Chair, Matthew L. Adler, Katharine D. Dukakis, Judge Karen Chaya Friedman, Mark Goodman, Ronald Ratner, Menachem Z. Rosensaft, and Kirk Rudy as members.